OL,3,CGuernsey's Standards Commissioner
OL,4,Cresigns
OL,6,FThe Commissioner subsequently
OL,7,Frecommended that Deputy St Pier be
OL,8,Fsuspended for 25 days without pay.
OL,10,FHowever, politicians largely backed
OL,11,FDeputy St Pier following a debate
OL,12,Fwhich saw 22 politicians vote against
OL,13,Fhis suspension and 11 support it.
OL,15,FAs a result, Dr McCullough has written
OL,16,Fa letter to the States Assembly and
OL,17,FConstitution Committee saying:
OL,19,F"There has been considerable
OL,20,Fcommentary, including continued
OL,21,Fmisrepresentation of key facts."
